{"body":"[{\"data\":1,\"prerenderedAt\":111},[\"ShallowReactive\",2],{\"project-en-\\u002Fprojects\\u002Fhsbc-digital-banking\":3},{\"id\":4,\"title\":5,\"architecture\":6,\"body\":7,\"category\":81,\"challenge\":82,\"company\":83,\"description\":84,\"extension\":85,\"featured\":86,\"meta\":87,\"metrics\":88,\"navigation\":95,\"order\":96,\"path\":97,\"period\":98,\"results\":99,\"role\":100,\"seo\":101,\"stack\":102,\"status\":108,\"stem\":109,\"__hash__\":110},\"projects_en\\u002Fen\\u002Fprojects\\u002Fhsbc-digital-banking.md\",\"Digital Banking Expansion\",\"Expanded the microservice ecosystem with event-driven services. Introduced a feature-flag system for progressive rollouts. Kafka event store enabled CQRS for read-optimized dashboards.\",{\"type\":8,\"value\":9,\"toc\":74},\"minimark\",[10,15,19,23,30,36,42,46],[11,12,14],\"h2\",{\"id\":13},\"challenge\",\"Challenge\",[16,17,18],\"p\",{},\"HSBC needed to ship digital banking features faster. The existing microservice platform had grown organically, but each new feature required coordinated releases across 8 teams. A single bad deployment could affect all customers.\",[11,20,22],{\"id\":21},\"architecture\",\"Architecture\",[16,24,25,29],{},[26,27,28],\"strong\",{},\"Event-driven expansion\",\": New services subscribed to domain events from the existing Kafka event store. No direct database coupling — services could be built and deployed independently.\",[16,31,32,35],{},[26,33,34],{},\"Feature flags\",\": Implemented a feature-flag service backed by Redis. New features were hidden behind flags and progressively rolled out: 5% (internal testing) → 25% (canary) → 100% (general availability). Bad features could be killed instantly without redeployment.\",[16,37,38,41],{},[26,39,40],{},\"CQRS for dashboards\",\": Read-heavy dashboards (account summary, transaction history) used a CQRS pattern — events from the write side were projected into optimized read models. Dashboards queried pre-built projections instead of aggregating on the fly.\",[11,43,45],{\"id\":44},\"results\",\"Results\",[47,48,49,56,62,68],\"ul\",{},[50,51,52,55],\"li\",{},[26,53,54],{},\"15+ features shipped\",\" in 18 months — previously would have taken 3+ years at old cadence\",[50,57,58,61],{},[26,59,60],{},\"Time-to-market\",\": 3 months → 3 weeks per feature\",[50,63,64,67],{},[26,65,66],{},\"Zero-downtime releases\",\": Feature flags enabled instant rollback\",[50,69,70,73],{},[26,71,72],{},\"Dashboard latency\",\": CQRS projections reduced query time from 2s to 200ms\",{\"title\":75,\"searchDepth\":76,\"depth\":76,\"links\":77},\"\",2,[78,79,80],{\"id\":13,\"depth\":76,\"text\":14},{\"id\":21,\"depth\":76,\"text\":22},{\"id\":44,\"depth\":76,\"text\":45},\"banking\",\"HSBC's digital banking platform needed new features fast — but the existing architecture required coordinated releases across 8 teams. Time-to-market for new features was 3+ months.\",\"Globant\",\"Expanded microservices and modernized its digital banking platform\",\"md\",false,{},[89,92],{\"label\":90,\"value\":91},\"Features shipped\",\"15+\",{\"label\":93,\"value\":94},\"Time to market\",\"-65%\",true,5,\"\\u002Fen\\u002Fprojects\\u002Fhsbc-digital-banking\",\"2020-2022\",\"Shipped 15+ new banking features in 18 months. Time-to-market reduced from 3 months to 3 weeks. Feature flags enabled safe progressive rollout to 5% → 25% → 100% of users.\",\"Java Microservices Developer\",{\"title\":5,\"description\":84},[103,104,105,106,107],\"Java\",\"Spring Boot\",\"Microservices\",\"Kafka\",\"Redis\",\"shipped\",\"en\\u002Fprojects\\u002Fhsbc-digital-banking\",\"MkSDrXTqtYRlyKTCStM4wGdEtnN65OzPTE3uZ-e-I-A\",1783828259358]","statusCode":200,"statusMessage":"","headers":{"content-type":"application/json;charset=utf-8","x-powered-by":"Nuxt"}}